\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\family typewriter
main()
\family default
 undergoes some prominent changes to get the two codebases working together,
 but it mostly consists of combining the two 
\family typewriter
main()
\family default
 functions,
 allowing them to work in concert.
 Most of the logic happens with the HTTP endpoint call in 
\family typewriter
handle_button()
\family default
.
 Surprisingly,
 once we did this,
 the entire thing worked out of the box;
 we were capable of sending text messages to our e-mails,
 and composing them with the universal remote.
 The steps from Section 
